entries.femaleVariant: No, I'm not OK, nothing's OK... Fuck.
I know one thing. This fucking city – I will not miss it.
I really can't understand it. After all that happened in Mikoshi... you feel no need to leave this shithole?
Just... leave. Run and never look back. Run away with me.
[Drink coffee]
Everything all right? You OK?
entries.maleVariant: Is everything all right? You OK?

entries.femaleVariant: Panam...
I need air.
Night City's my city. Still got something to prove here.
entries.maleVariant: Night City's my city. Still got somethin' left to prove here.

entries.femaleVariant: Even if I leave with you, my time's almost up.
Why don't you stay here with me?
We talked about this. You know I got unfinished biz here, one more job to take care of.
So what? You also have everyone at the Afterlife eating out of your hand. You don't need any more jobs, you have it all! Shit, just open your eyes!
I have it all? You sure...? 'Cause all includes you, Panam. Stay here. With me.
I can't! They are my clan, my family, my responsibility. And yet you ask me to choose. Why, V, for what?
For Night City. I still have something to prove to it.
entries.maleVariant: For Night City. Still got somethin' to prove here.

entries.femaleVariant: Even if I run away with you, I'll still be short on time. You know that.
entries.maleVariant: Say I run away with you. Still be short on time. You know that.

entries.femaleVariant: Night City is my city.
Night City is a cancer. Just… look what it's done to you!
Got somethin' left to prove. Night City'll have its new legend. Deserves it. I deserve it.
No. Fucking listen to yourself. I know what's happening to you, what happened in Mikoshi. But…
Will fame be any comfort when you die here alone, some yes-mercs from the Afterlife at your side?
You don't understand, Panam.
You better fucking believe I don't. Everything you do here will be dust swept away by whoever comes after you.
V, I... I will be gone tomorrow. There will be no more "us." Do you understand that?
Don't wanna lose you. But there's no other way.
I'm dying. Lemme settle my affairs.
So this is goodbye?
So – this is goodbye.
What would it change if I did leave with you? Only got a few months left anyway.
It would be a few months among people you care about. People who care about you.
Unless... unless that's your point. You think the end could be easier... if you were alone?
You know that's not true.
I know this, V. Tomorrow, I will be gone. We're breaking camp, we'll leave at dawn.
Don't wanna lose you, but I can't leave... Can't live or think any other way.
Well, you know I always set my radio to Stanley. Will I hear about you?
You can bet on it.
Fuck. I so detest goodbyes.
I'm dying, Panam.
See you, Panam. Someday.
We don't have to say goodbye.
Fuck, you think I don't know that? We've talked about--
Wait. Lemme finish.
This last job – it's important. Probably the most important job of my life. And if I can get it done…
entries.maleVariant: This last job – it's important. Prolly the most important job of my life. And if I can get it done…

entries.femaleVariant: You will have finally proven to yourself that you're the best. Something everyone else knows. And you will see how you're addicted to the thought.
No. I'll prove to myself that all this city gave me or took from me – that it was for a reason.
I understand. I think.
Can you let me do this?
Fuck.
Do the damn job. Show this fucking city who's boss. And realize, finally, that it was never about one last mission. You just don't know any other way…
I promise.
See you around, Panam.
Until next time. Somewhere, someday.
Remember, you still owe me that story about the guy from Kaukaz. One who rode in your trunk.
Oh, it's a great fucking story. But a long one. Many twists and turns.
I'll try to find the time.
Damn right you will.
Gotta go – Afterlife awaits.
I should go, too. Take care, V. And good luck.
Thanks.
They had a saying in my clan – "No goodbyes, only roads that fork and converge."
And promise me one thing. That you will not lose your way. Not in the final stretch.
I will remember, V. Always.
Nomads say all sorts of shit.
Speaking of which… you still owe me that story of the guy from Kaukaz. One who rode in your trunk.
entries.maleVariant: Speaking of which… you still owe me that story of that guy from Kaukaz. One who rode in your trunk.

entries.femaleVariant: I'll tell you. Someday, somewhere. If our roads meet again.
[Take shower] Didn't wanna wait for me?
Hey. Hop on in.
What, couldn't wait for me?
[Stand]
Everything all right?
Fuck...
[Wash off blood]
[Lean]
[Hug] Till next time.
[Step away] Gotta go – Afterlife awaits.
[Turn]
Wanna see the Crystal Palace?
Wanna do some Crystal Palace-spottin'?
To hell with that Palace. V... I...
I didn't want to wake you.
Till next time.
Go on. They're waiting, counting on you.
Fingers crossed, toes too.
[Take amulet]
